      • recursiveBinarySearch

        public static int recursiveBinarySearch(int[] array,
                                        int key,
                                        int left,
                                        int right)

        This is the implementation of a binary search over an integer list.

        This method requires that list is sorted and then we search for key in the sub-array: array[left]....array[right], including BOTH ends.
        Parameters:
        array - Must be sorted in increasing order.
        key - The integer that we are looking for.
        left - The first index of the sub-array over which to search
        right - The last index of the sub-array over which to search,
        Returns:
        -1 if the key is not in the array. A positive index in [left,right] if key is in the array.
